00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:25.360
When you were a kid, what did you use to bake?

00:01:30.260 --> 00:01:32.260
Well, Marion asks what was the recipe I used to do most

00:01:32.260 --> 00:01:33.614
when I was a kid

00:01:33.614 --> 00:01:34.578
Without hesitation : crepes !

00:01:34.578 --> 00:01:36.514
I started real soon

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:39.080
my tradition each year was that

00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:40.600
the first crepe I cooked

00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:43.580
i usually decorated it with coins and other "magic" stuffs

00:01:47.014 --> 00:01:49.014
and would let it dry out on top of my parents's kitchen

00:01:50.700 --> 00:01:52.700
That was supposed to bring wealth and good luck for the year !!

00:01:53.633 --> 00:01:55.633
Once I was cleaning the kitchen maybe around 16 or 17

00:01:55.633 --> 00:01:57.140
and there were like 10 dried crepes

00:01:59.754 --> 00:02:01.754
they were like crepes mummies !

00:02:04.489 --> 00:02:06.489
so crepes is the answer

00:02:06.489 --> 00:02:07.840
and so if you have kids, 

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:09.595
let them cook crepes,

00:02:10.067 --> 00:02:12.067
you never know, it can give them a taste for cooking later :)

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.300
How did you fall in love with cooking?

00:02:19.980 --> 00:02:21.980
I was asked this question by many fans

00:02:22.020 --> 00:02:24.020
how did it all start?

00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:25.400
I think we need to go back to my childhood

00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:28.720
my parents would let me cook, experiment

00:02:31.040 --> 00:02:33.040
the only condition was that I cleaned the mess afterwards...

00:02:34.793 --> 00:02:36.793
and then as a student

00:02:36.793 --> 00:02:38.160
I left my parents' house at 17 for my studies

00:02:38.220 --> 00:02:40.220
and had no choice, I was on my own :)

00:02:43.053 --> 00:02:45.053
I started with simple things like pastas

00:02:45.954 --> 00:02:47.954
but i would prepare my own tomatoe sauce

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.000
I remember I didn't have an oven

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:53.640
so I would bake my cakes in the microwave !

00:02:56.960 --> 00:02:58.960
Like my 5 minutes brownies recipe

00:02:59.174 --> 00:03:01.174
it dates back from when I was a student

00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:07.660
and trust me, this particular chocolate brownie

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:09.134
help me make a lot of friends at the time :)

